summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 25199, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the City Engineer to incur an indebtedness in the sum of $2709.41 against the General Fund of The City of Seattle, on account of the cost and expense of the improvement of Twentieth Avenue South et al., by paving the same, as authorized by Ordinance No. 23438, creating Local Improvement District No. 2271," approved September 29th, 1910.
